WEBVTT

00:01:01.840 --> 00:01:04.310
Well, good evening, family. Thank you

00:01:04.320 --> 00:01:06.790
for joining us again today.

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:08.590
We're going to go over

00:01:08.600 --> 00:01:10.990
some things some people have had

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:14.070
questions concerning our ministry

00:01:14.080 --> 00:01:16.390
and why we're named what we're named and

00:01:16.400 --> 00:01:17.990
all things like that. So, we want to

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:19.630
clear some things up because we've had

00:01:19.640 --> 00:01:21.590
some emails. Some are not so nice.

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:23.630
People are pretty upset about things

00:01:23.640 --> 00:01:26.110
being, you know, sister clipboards

00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:26.120
or

00:01:26.120 --> 00:01:27.190
whatever you want to call them because

00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:29.510
they don't understand. But Diana wants

00:01:29.520 --> 00:01:31.830
to explain the foundation part of our

00:01:31.840 --> 00:01:33.150
name.

00:01:33.160 --> 00:01:35.830
We are not a foundation, for sure.

00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:37.470
I want you to know that we are not a

00:01:37.480 --> 00:01:39.910
foundation. We picked the name

00:01:39.920 --> 00:01:42.590
because prayer is a foundation,

00:01:42.600 --> 00:01:46.070
but we're an online church, and

00:01:46.080 --> 00:01:48.390
so the Prayer Changes Things Foundation

00:01:48.400 --> 00:01:50.190
is an online church if you see that in

00:01:50.200 --> 00:01:52.710
the description that we put in there.

00:01:52.720 --> 00:01:55.190
We have weekly online

00:01:55.200 --> 00:01:58.750
services, and so under US federal law,

00:01:58.760 --> 00:02:00.950
churches are automatically recognized as

00:02:00.950 --> 00:02:00.960
tax-exempt

00:02:00.960 --> 00:02:04.070
under section 501(c)(3) of the

00:02:04.080 --> 00:02:05.310
IRS

00:02:05.320 --> 00:02:07.950
and are not required to apply for formal

00:02:07.960 --> 00:02:10.510
recognition. So, we have an EIN and all

00:02:10.520 --> 00:02:12.710
of that, but we don't have to do

00:02:12.720 --> 00:02:13.590
what

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:16.270
some of the more... like Joseph Z's

00:02:16.280 --> 00:02:19.070
ministry has a board and all. There

00:02:19.070 --> 00:02:19.080
are

00:02:19.080 --> 00:02:20.150
more

00:02:20.160 --> 00:02:22.030
requirements and stuff that they all do,

00:02:22.040 --> 00:02:24.470
but churches are also specifically

00:02:24.480 --> 00:02:26.949
exempt from the Form 990 filing

00:02:26.959 --> 00:02:28.790
requirement under

00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:33.750
the Internal Revenue Code 6033A

00:02:33.750 --> 00:02:33.760
3 AI.

00:02:33.760 --> 00:02:36.230
So, everything we've done—I want

00:02:36.240 --> 00:02:38.230
to say this because people want to know

00:02:38.230 --> 00:02:38.240
because

00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:40.310
it's tax

00:02:40.310 --> 00:02:40.320
season—everything

00:02:40.320 --> 00:02:42.510
we have done, we have

00:02:42.510 --> 00:02:42.520
gone

00:02:42.520 --> 00:02:44.630
through lawyers. We have

00:02:44.630 --> 00:02:44.640
gone

00:02:44.640 --> 00:02:47.350
through

00:02:47.360 --> 00:02:48.790
people that have set it up that have

00:02:48.800 --> 00:02:52.110
been professional. My wife

00:02:52.120 --> 00:02:55.590
has a Master's degree in

00:02:55.600 --> 00:02:57.150
accounting. So, a lot of times you say,

00:02:57.160 --> 00:02:59.870
'Well, Brandon, how come Diana is not on

00:02:59.880 --> 00:03:01.910
