and

00:45:04.480 --> 00:45:07.070
we saved back. We saved back

00:45:07.080 --> 00:45:10.310
some more because the Bible tells us, 'Owe no

00:45:15.520 --> 00:45:18.510
man anything but to love

00:45:18.510 --> 00:45:18.520
him.'Sorry,

00:45:18.520 --> 00:45:21.350
I'm tired tonight, y'all.

00:45:26.080 --> 00:45:26.990
You're done. I don't want to show him

00:45:26.990 --> 00:45:27.000
any

00:45:27.000 --> 00:45:31.390
more. It's embarrassing.

00:45:31.400 --> 00:45:32.910
You know, when you look at that, you go,

00:45:32.920 --> 00:45:34.230
'My God,

00:45:34.240 --> 00:45:35.910
we're just

00:45:35.910 --> 00:45:35.920
transparent.'It's

00:45:35.920 --> 00:45:37.630
real.

00:45:37.630 --> 00:45:37.640
Twenty

00:45:37.640 --> 00:45:39.670
years.

00:45:39.680 --> 00:45:42.430
Oh, Jesus used to visit me in here.

00:45:42.440 --> 00:45:44.190
I used to sit in here on the floor. I

00:45:44.200 --> 00:45:45.790
want you to look at that.

00:45:45.800 --> 00:45:46.670
Just being real with you. You

00:45:46.680 --> 00:45:48.390
see, Jesus visited me in here. That's

00:45:48.400 --> 00:45:51.230
where I raised the dog from the dead.

00:45:51.240 --> 00:45:53.470
The dog was dead in the

00:45:53.480 --> 00:45:55.390
room. And I had my washing

00:45:55.400 --> 00:45:57.350
machine. There was an old cabinet behind

00:45:57.360 --> 00:45:59.310
there and I tore it out because I needed

00:45:59.320 --> 00:46:01.670
room. And so, I'm just being

00:46:01.680 --> 00:46:02.950
real with y'all,

00:46:02.960 --> 00:46:05.310
that's where Jesus raised the dog

00:46:05.320 --> 00:46:09.830
from the dead.

00:46:09.840 --> 00:46:11.430
Poverty.

00:46:11.440 --> 00:46:15.430
All three of our kids were born there.

00:46:15.440 --> 00:46:18.470
But Diana made it through college.

00:46:18.480 --> 00:46:20.030
And we

00:46:20.040 --> 00:46:21.630
got through it, didn't we?

00:46:21.640 --> 00:46:23.550
Making minimum wage. I

00:46:23.550 --> 00:46:23.560
made

00:46:23.560 --> 00:46:26.470
less than $17,000 a year

00:46:26.480 --> 00:46:34.190
after taxes. But

00:46:34.190 --> 00:46:34.200
God,

00:46:34.200 --> 00:46:36.350
but God.

00:46:38.200 --> 00:46:39.350
So

00:46:39.360 --> 00:46:40.390
people are going to hate whatever they

00:46:40.400 --> 00:46:41.310
want to do, but they don't know where

00:46:41.320 --> 00:46:42.470
you come from

00:46:42.480 --> 00:46:45.190
and what you sow to get there.

00:46:45.200 --> 00:46:46.950
God's always good and God is always

00:46:46.960 --> 00:46:48.550
faithful. But I'm trying to tell you,

00:46:48.560 --> 00:46:51.230
don't give up on your dreams

00:46:51.230 --> 00:46:51.240
because

00:46:51.240 --> 00:46:53.430
right now, like I said, I have seven

00:46:53.440 --> 00:46:55.590
channels and we minister to people all

00:46:55.600 --> 00:46:57.510
around the world

00:46:57.520 --> 00:46:59.110
on a day-to-day

00:46:59.120 --> 00:47:01.590
basis. It's not us; no,

00:47:01.600 --> 00:47:04.590
it's Him. We had over 225

00:47:04.600 --> 00:47:06.070
salvations

00:47:12.680 --> 00:47:14.190
this

00:47:14.200 --> 00:47:15.670
last video.

00:47:15.680 --> 00:47:20.390
Isn't that wonderful?

00:47:20.400 --> 00:47:22.470
But when you listen to Him

00:47:22.480 --> 00:47:24.070
and you're faithful and you're

00:47:24.070 --> 00:47:24.080
a

00:47:24.080 --> 00:47:26.070
consistent

00:47:28.840 --> 00:47:29.750
tither—we

00:47:31.720 --> 00:47:34.310
tithed even

00:47:34.320 --> 00:47:36.590
when we didn't have it. We weren't doing what we wanted to; we were forced to tithe. We tithed even when we didn't want to because if

00:47:36.600 --> 00:47:38.910
we didn't tithe, they fired us.

00:47:38.920 --> 00:47:40.590
We tithed even off of what we had,

00:47:40.600 --> 00:47:41.870
and if you didn't tithe, they

00:47:41.880 --> 00:47:42.710
fired you. We

00:47:42.710 --> 00:47:42.720
didn't

00:47:42.720 --> 00:47:44.150
have enough to pay our bills after we

00:47:44.160 --> 00:47:47.750
tithed, and we did it for

00:47:47.750 --> 00:47:47.760
thirteen

00:47:47.760 --> 00:47:49.190
years.

00:47:49.200 --> 00:47:50.630
We tithed and tithed.

00:47:50.640 --> 00:47:52.270
When

00:47:52.280 --> 00:47:54.030
you're consistent with your

00:47:54.030 --> 00:47:54.040
tithe—because

00:47:54.040 --> 00:47:57.910
your boss forces you to

00:47:57.910 --> 00:47:57.920
tithe—we

00:47:57.920 --> 00:48:00.670
learned how to

00:48:00.670 --> 00:48:00.680
tithe.

00:48:00.680 --> 00:48:03.230
It's because of that we learned.

00:48:03.240 --> 00:48:05.110
And the Lord will

00:48:05.120 --> 00:48:07.150
bless your hands. That's why I

00:48:07.160 --> 00:48:08.310
try to tell you all that you have

00:48:08.310 --> 00:48:08.320
tithers'rights.

00:48:08.320 --> 00:48:10.710
I believe with all my

00:48:10.720 --> 00:48:12.910
heart that God will bless you in the

00:48:12.920 --> 00:48:14.550
city and in the field, coming in and going

00:48:14.560 --> 00:48:16.790
out. When you come from nothing, if you

00:48:16.800 --> 00:48:19.390
give Him your finances and you

00:48:19.400 --> 00:48:21.270
give and you sow

00:48:21.280 --> 00:48:22.590
regardless,

00:48:22.600 --> 00:48:24.870
He'll bring you out of nothing.

00:48:24.880 --> 00:48:27.270
He'll give you an idea.

00:48:27.280 --> 00:48:29.270
And it all started when Diana said,

00:48:30.720 --> 00:48:31.910
'I'll go to college. I'll get my

00:48:31.920 --> 00:48:34.070
master's. It will take us through

00:48:34.070 --> 00:48:34.080
this.'And

00:48:34.080 --> 00:48:35.630
I thought she was never going to. She

00:48:35.640 --> 00:48:36.950
went to night school while I watched the

00:48:36.960 --> 00:48:38.070
kids.

00:48:38.080 --> 00:48:41.070
I cried myself to sleep. I remember

00:48:41.080 --> 00:48:42.550
every night I'd say, 'Lord, I don't

00:48:42.560 --> 00:48:43.750
know how I'm going to get all this

00:48:43.760 --> 00:48:45.470
done today:

00:48:45.480 --> 00:48:47.110
all the homework, all the essays I had

00:48:47.120 --> 00:48:49.870
to write.'Because she was working full-time

00:48:49.880 --> 00:48:52.510
and after she got off work, she would go

00:48:52.520 --> 00:48:54.750
to school until the wee hours in the

00:48:54.760 --> 00:48:55.750
morning

00:48:55.760 --> 00:48:57.590
and then come home and do her homework;

00:48:57.600 --> 00:48:59.190
some nights she'd get only two hours of

00:48:59.200 --> 00:49:02.510
sleep. She did that for years.

00:49:02.520 --> 00:49:04.310
Then she'd get up the next day and

00:49:04.320 --> 00:49:06.510
go to work all day long and do things

00:49:06.520 --> 00:49:08.750
for the church. Both

00:49:08.760 --> 00:49:10.790
of us—I watched the kids while

00:49:10.800 --> 00:49:12.750
she was going to school

00:49:12.760 --> 00:49:15.270
and we worked our butts off to get where

00:49:15.280 --> 00:49:17.430
we got.

00:49:17.440 --> 00:49:19.510
Finally, after eight years, I'll never

00:49:19.520 --> 00:49:20.830
forget when she said, 'Honey, I'm

00:49:20.840 --> 00:49:22.790
finished my last

00:49:22.790 --> 00:49:22.800
class.'She

00:49:22.800 --> 00:49:25.230
graduated, and when she graduated summa

00:49:25.230 --> 00:49:25.240
cum

00:49:25.240 --> 00:49:27.150
laude, she was top of her

00:49:27.160 --> 00:49:30.270
class. I looked at her and said,

00:49:30.280 --> 00:49:32.830
'My God, it's really over.

00:49:32.840 --> 00:49:34.390
We don't have to do school all night

00:49:34.400 --> 00:49:36.630
and I can spend time with you

00:49:36.640 --> 00:49:39.030
and talk.'After eight years, I

00:49:39.030 --> 00:49:39.040
felt

00:49:39.040 --> 00:49:41.430
like I hardly knew her anymore because she

00:49:41.440 --> 00:49:43.590
did it all weekend long;

00:49:43.600 --> 00:49:45.990
she was doing full-time school.

00:49:46.000 --> 00:49:48.350
Megan's therapies and everything

00:49:48.360 --> 00:49:50.390
cost a lot. Well, that

00:49:50.400 --> 00:49:51.670
was me;

00:49:51.680 --> 00:49:53.910
I was doing that with all I had,

00:49:53.920 --> 00:49:55.470
watching her and taking her to

00:49:55.480 --> 00:49:57.550
things while you were doing school.

00:49:57.560 --> 00:50:01.830
I'd go by myself.

00:50:01.840 --> 00:50:03.470
But I always want

00:50:03.480 --> 00:50:05.390
to present this stuff to you—it's not

00:50:05.400 --> 00:50:07.830
a sob story;

00:50:07.840 --> 00:50:10.030
it's our story. Well,

00:50:10.040 --> 00:50:11.910
when I walked across that

00:50:11.920 --> 00:50:13.670
stage,

00:50:13.680 --> 00:50:15.270
I felt like He walked across it with me.

00:50:15.280 --> 00:50:16.990
I was like, 'He's the

00:50:17.000 --> 00:50:19.350
one that helped me get

00:50:19.350 --> 00:50:19.360
it.'The

00:50:19.360 --> 00:50:23.070
dean of ORU laid hands on her. I

00:50:23.080 --> 00:50:25.230
couldn't go in with her to her

00:50:25.240 --> 00:50:26.550
dinner because they were celebrating her

00:50:26.550 --> 00:50:26.560
because

00:50:26.560 --> 00:50:28.510
she got summa cum laude

00:50:28.520 --> 00:50:30.230
and she had to go in by herself because

00:50:30.240 --> 00:50:32.910
Megan was so bad at that time. I sat

00:50:32.920 --> 00:50:34.790
out in the car with Megan.

00:50:34.800 --> 00:50:37.590
Diana was pregnant—I

00:50:37.590 --> 00:50:37.600
didn't

00:50:37.600 --> 00:50:41.070
know it.

00:50:41.070 --> 00:50:41.080
Actually,

00:50:41.080 --> 00:50:43.190
you weren't pregnant yet.

00:50:43.200 --> 00:50:46.630
You walked in

00:50:46.640 --> 00:50:48.190
and the man said,

00:50:48.200 --> 00:50:50.710
'I don't know who you are,

00:50:50.720 --> 00:50:52.270
but the Lord told me to give you a

00:50:52.280 --> 00:50:54.070
word. I'm supposed to lay hands

00:50:54.080 --> 00:50:55.870
on you. You're called to the nations.

00:50:55.880 --> 00:50:57.630
You're going to be a prophetic voice to

00:50:57.640 --> 00:50:58.990
the nations. You and your husband are

00:50:59.000 --> 00:51:00.510
going to walk in a great call in the end

00:51:00.520 --> 00:51:01.990
times

00:51:02.000 --> 00:51:03.350
and you're going to lead

00:51:03.360 --> 00:51:05.470
many to

00:51:06.470 --> 00:51:06.480
Jesus.'So

00:51:07.760 --> 00:51:09.750
he laid hands on her, and I remember

00:51:09.760 --> 00:51:11.350
sitting there when she came out and

00:51:11.360 --> 00:51:12.950
said, 'Brandon, I got a prophetic

00:51:12.960 --> 00:51:14.710
word from the

00:51:14.710 --> 00:51:14.720
dean.'I

00:51:14.720 --> 00:51:17.470
said, 'What? Oh, I wish I could

00:51:17.480 --> 00:51:20.110
have been there.'So she told

00:51:20.120 --> 00:51:21.710
me all about it. But I was sitting out

00:51:21.720 --> 00:51:23.710
with Megan in the car,

00:51:23.720 --> 00:51:26.270
and I was so excited that we got that

00:51:26.280 --> 00:51:28.030
prophetic word.

00:51:28.040 --> 00:51:30.790
It gave me hope because Megan was

00:51:30.790 --> 00:51:30.800
struggling

00:51:30.800 --> 00:51:32.790
at that time. She wouldn't wear

00:51:32.800 --> 00:51:34.630
clothes and she used to wear diapers all

00:51:34.640 --> 00:51:35.830
the time.

00:51:35.830 --> 00:51:35.840
She

00:51:35.840 --> 00:51:37.150
used

00:51:37.150 --> 00:51:37.160
to

00:51:37.160 --> 00:51:37.190
take

00:51:37.190 --> 00:51:37.200
her

00:51:37.200 --> 00:51:38.950
clothes off whenever she got in the car.

00:51:38.960 --> 00:51:41.630
She didn't like the texture—the way it

00:51:41.630 --> 00:51:41.640
felt on her.

00:51:41.640 --> 00:51:43.110
You guys have no

00:51:43.120 --> 00:51:45.590
idea; she's come so far. It's been

00:51:45.600 --> 00:51:46.270
little by little.

00:51:46.280 --> 00:51:48.030
We were so excited the day she started wearing

00:51:48.040 --> 00:51:49.230
clothes

00:51:49.240 --> 00:51:51.030
because the texture of the clothes

00:51:51.040 --> 00:51:53.390
on her skin made her freak out. It was

00:51:53.400 --> 00:51:54.550
bad.

00:51:54.560 --> 00:51:56.470
But just saying, every single thing you

00:51:56.480 --> 00:51:58.750
go through along the

00:51:58.760 --> 00:52:00.350
way—like

00:52:00.360 --> 00:52:01.790
we always try to talk to you a

00:52:01.800 --> 00:52:03.630
little bit before we

00:52:03.630 --> 00:52:03.640
pray—I

00:52:03.640 --> 00:52:06.070
want to give you hope

00:52:06.080 --> 00:52:09.190
that if God can take somebody

00:52:09.200 --> 00:52:11.110
that had nothing

00:52:11.120 --> 00:52:13.510
and do what He's done with me

00:52:13.520 --> 00:52:15.230
and with her,

00:52:15.240 --> 00:52:17.390
God can do it with anybody.

00:52:17.400 --> 00:52:19.630
You just have to be faithful in your

00:52:19.640 --> 00:52:20.790
giving.

00:52:20.800 --> 00:52:22.430
You have to be faithful in what God's

00:52:22.440 --> 00:52:24.150
called you to do. Be faithful to your

00:52:24.160 --> 00:52:27.350
church. Wherever you go to church,

00:52:27.360 --> 00:52:29.070
honor that pastor.

00:52:29.080 --> 00:52:31.990
Tithe there, give there. Bless them;

00:52:32.000 --> 00:52:34.110
help

00:52:34.110 --> 00:52:34.120
him.

00:52:34.120 --> 00:52:35.830
You say, 'Well, I'm only able to

00:52:35.840 --> 00:52:37.870
do this.'Well, I believe with all my

00:52:37.880 --> 00:52:40.670
heart that God stretches your dollar.

00:52:40.670 --> 00:52:40.680
I

00:52:40.680 --> 00:52:43.190
know because I lived it.

00:52:43.190 --> 00:52:43.200
We

00:52:43.200 --> 00:52:44.670
were

00:52:44.680 --> 00:52:46.990
on food stamps, but

00:52:47.000 --> 00:52:48.830
we made it.

00:52:48.840 --> 00:52:50.350
We made it through.

00:52:50.360 --> 00:52:52.910
And you get to the end of

00:52:52.920 --> 00:52:55.510
your whole journey and you have

00:52:55.520 --> 00:52:58.950
memories to tell of your faith journey.

00:52:58.960 --> 00:53:01.110
It's adventures in faith,

00:53:01.120 --> 00:53:03.190
journeys in faith. That's what

00:53:03.190 --> 00:53:03.200
Diana

00:53:04.230 --> 00:53:04.240
and

00:53:04.240 --> 00:53:07.030
I

00:53:07.040 --> 00:53:09.590
were.

00:53:09.600 --> 00:53:11.830
We lived

00:53:11.840 --> 00:53:14.430
a hard time with Megan.

00:53:21.840 --> 00:53:24.110
I know there's a lot of you that have

00:53:24.120 --> 00:53:25.710
lost children

00:53:25.710 --> 00:53:25.720
and

00:53:25.720 --> 00:53:27.070
you go, 'Brandon, what's your sob

00:53:27.080 --> 00:53:28.990
story? I lost my kid. My kid passed

00:53:29.000 --> 00:53:29.950
away.

00:53:29.960 --> 00:53:32.510
You still have your

00:53:32.510 --> 00:53:32.520
daughter.'It

00:53:32.520 --> 00:53:34.430
felt like a death to us

00:53:34.440 --> 00:53:36.670
every day. It felt like a death that

00:53:36.680 --> 00:53:39.710
wouldn't go away.

00:53:39.720 --> 00:53:41.710
If you lose a child, you

00:53:41.720 --> 00:53:43.550
bury them and you grieve them and you

00:53:43.560 --> 00:53:45.550
still have their memory. But whenever I

00:53:45.560 --> 00:53:47.430
woke up to the memory of my daughter

00:53:47.440 --> 00:53:49.710
never going to live a normal life, it

00:53:49.720 --> 00:53:51.790
was like facing death every single day

00:53:51.800 --> 00:53:53.990
in my heart, every

00:53:54.000 --> 00:53:54.470
birthday.

00:53:54.480 --> 00:53:55.790
I'm not trying to knock; I'm trying

00:53:55.800 --> 00:53:57.910
to tell you what I felt. I

00:53:57.920 --> 00:53:58.990
can't

00:53:59.000 --> 00:54:01.070
imagine losing a child,

00:54:01.080 --> 00:54:02.550
but it's what it felt like to me.

00:54:05.560 --> 00:54:08.310
She turns 21

00:54:08.320 --> 00:54:09.430
next week.

00:54:12.760 --> 00:54:14.990
Her birthday is

00:54:15.000 --> 00:54:16.470
March 18th.

00:54:20.560 --> 00:54:22.910
I'm so thankful for her. She's a

00:54:22.920 --> 00:54:25.830
blessing. We love her.

00:54:26.720 --> 00:54:31.110
Megan has come a long

00:54:31.110 --> 00:54:31.120
way,

00:54:31.120 --> 00:54:32.910
but like I said, I

00:54:37.040 --> 00:54:38.830
try to give you hope

00:54:38.830 --> 00:54:38.840
because

00:54:38.840 --> 00:54:40.590
I know I speak to people that live

00:54:40.600 --> 00:54:42.910
in villages, people that live

00:54:42.910 --> 00:54:42.920
with

00:54:42.920 --> 00:54:45.070
barely anything in all parts

00:54:45.080 --> 00:54:45.950
of the world. And you say, 'Well,

00:54:45.960 --> 00:54:47.590
Brandon, you look like you got a

00:54:47.600 --> 00:54:49.470
lot.'I'm

00:54:49.480 --> 00:54:51.150
going to tell you this: in

00:54:51.160 --> 00:54:53.830
America, that's not a lot.

00:54:53.840 --> 00:54:56.510
In

00:54:56.520 --> 00:54:58.430
Oklahoma,

00:54:58.440 --> 00:55:01.070
we had crack dealers on one

00:55:01.080 --> 00:55:03.790
side cooking meth in their house. We had

00:55:03.800 --> 00:55:06.390
drug busts in front of

00:55:06.400 --> 00:55:08.470
us and they would get on top of our roof,

00:55:08.480 --> 00:55:10.590
high as a kite, and throw beers at my

00:55:10.600 --> 00:55:12.070
dogs.

00:55:12.070 --> 00:55:12.080
They'd

00:55:12.080 --> 00:55:14.590
get on the

00:55:14.600 --> 00:55:16.350
roof and just jump around in

00:55:16.360 --> 00:55:18.110
the middle of the night.

00:55:18.120 --> 00:55:19.630
I kid you not.

00:55:19.640 --> 00:55:20.990
They would

00:55:21.000 --> 00:55:23.470
throw their whiskey and their crap at my

00:55:23.480 --> 00:55:25.070
dogs trying to knock them out because they

00:55:25.080 --> 00:55:26.630
were barking, trying to tell on them that

00:55:26.640 --> 00:55:28.230
they were in my yard.

00:55:28.240 --> 00:55:29.830
I had little dogs I was raising

00:55:33.080 --> 00:55:34.310
and they would throw those alcohol

00:55:34.320 --> 00:55:37.150
bottles and they would hit my dogs

00:55:37.160 --> 00:55:38.550
and I'd have to call the police.

00:55:38.560 --> 00:55:39.830
My grandma would be

00:55:39.840 --> 00:55:40.830
over there because she lived across the

